# Group Access Token

Gets an `access_token` that authorizes you to make calls against the API. The API and methods you are authorized for depend on the API and scope that the `client_id` and `client_secret` were granted for. Note: the `{client_id}:{client_secret}` string sent in the Authorization header must be Base64 encoded.

## Retrieve Access Token [/access_token]

### POST

Operation: access_token_grant

+ Request

    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic {client_id}:{client_secret}
            Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

    + Body

            grant_type=client_credentials

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                access_token: 'abcdefg1234567',
                expires_in: 300
                token_type: 'Bearer'
            }

